data.content:
The upgrade pulls in **Microsoft.OpenApi v2**, which has several breaking changes. Here's what changed and the fixes:

| .NET 9 (OpenApi v1) | .NET 10 (OpenApi v2) |
|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any` namespace | **Removed** — use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` |
| `new OpenApiString("1.0")` | `JsonValue.Create("1.0")` |
| `schema.Nullable = false` | `schema.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` (flags enum) |
| `new OpenApiSecurityScheme { Reference = new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "..." } }` | `new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("...")` |

**Fixed code:**

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;          // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References; // for OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");   // was: new OpenApiString("1.0")
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("oauth2"); // typed reference replaces OpenApiReference
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;  // was: .Nullable = false
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

**Summary of changes:**
1. **`OpenApiString` → `JsonValue.Create()`** — all `IOpenApiAny` primitives are replaced by `JsonNode` types.
2. **`OpenApiReference` → typed reference classes** — instead of manually building an `OpenApiReference` with `ReferenceType`, use `OpenApiSecuritySchemeReference("id")` (also `OpenApiSchemaReference`, `OpenApiParameterReference`, etc. in `Microsoft.OpenApi.Models.References`).
3. **`Nullable` → `JsonSchemaType` flags** — OpenApi v2 follows JSON Schema where nullability is expressed as a type flag (`JsonSchemaType.Null`). Clear it with `&= ~`, set it with `|=`.
